unix-utils is a collection of useful unix utilities not included by
default in unix-like operating systems.

The utilites included are:
	btee - buffered pipe fitting
	lambda - create a shell script and print its path
	pick - interactively select lines from files
	slice - display portions of files

check out INSTALL for installation instructions. Check out the man
pages of each utility for usage info.

unix-utils was written by Sturm Mabie (sturm@cryptm.org)
